      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Religious groups should not be able to opt out of government laws if those laws conflict with their faith. Secularism is crucial for ensuring equality and preventing discrimination. A healthy democracy must uphold the separation of church and state to maintain fairness and protect the rights of all citizens. Allowing exceptions based on religious beliefs could lead to unequal treatment and undermine the principles of a secular, democratic society.",
